</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C30E38EA8E5C781E80FAFE36FB4AD842" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BAB6B618E5C781E80FAFE36FDAADF42" blockId="2.[166,1225,506,1077]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
R e d e s c r i p t i o n. Female (
<figureCitation id="132F77E48E5C781E823AFE36FDA7DE62" box="[539,602,506,532]" captionStart="Figs 1–5" captionStartId="3.[174,213,1802,1824]" captionTargetBox="[230,1169,173,1735]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 1–5. Sinodiaptomus sarsi: 1 — habitus of female (A) and male (B); 2 — last prosomal somite and urosome of female; 3 — leg 5, female; 4 — right antennule, male; 5 — leg 5, male." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6377804" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6377804/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">FIg. 1</figureCitation>
, 
<emphasis id="B960B7738E5C781E824AFE36FD83DE62" box="[619,638,506,532]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">A</emphasis>
). Body length (excluding furcal setae) 
<quantity id="4CECC6848E5C781E8476FE36FF2BDE42" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.27" metricValueMax="2.49" metricValueMin="2.05" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" unit="mm" value="2.27" valueMax="2.49" valueMin="2.05">2.05–2.49 mm</quantity>
(2.24 ± 
<quantity id="4CECC6848E5C781E8118FDD6FE5EDE42" box="[313,419,538,564]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" unit="mm" value="0.13">0.13 mm</quantity>
, n = 15), prosome length 
<quantity id="4CECC6848E5C781E82F4FDD6FC83DE42" box="[725,894,538,565]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" metricValueMax="1.75" metricValueMin="1.45" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" unit="mm" value="1.6" valueMax="1.75" valueMin="1.45">1.45–1.75 mm</quantity>
(1.58 ± 
<quantity id="4CECC6848E5C781E83C1FDD6FBB0DE42" box="[992,1101,538,564]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" unit="mm" value="0.09">0.09 mm</quantity>
), prosome width 
<quantity id="4CECC6848E5C781E80D2FDF6FE50DE22" box="[243,429,570,597]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.8" metricValueMax="6.5" metricValueMin="5.1" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" unit="mm" value="0.58" valueMax="0.65" valueMin="0.51">0.51 – 0.65 mm</quantity>
(0.58 ± 
<quantity id="4CECC6848E5C781E8233FDF6FD82DE22" box="[530,639,570,596]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" unit="mm" value="0.04">0.04 mm</quantity>
). The dorsal surface of last prosomal somite with a chitinous, triangular projection (
<figureCitation id="132F77E48E5C781E8260FD96FD82DE02" box="[577,639,602,628]" captionStart="Figs 1–5" captionStartId="3.[174,213,1802,1824]" captionTargetBox="[230,1169,173,1735]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 1–5. Sinodiaptomus sarsi: 1 — habitus of female (A) and male (B); 2 — last prosomal somite and urosome of female; 3 — leg 5, female; 4 — right antennule, male; 5 — leg 5, male." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6377804" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6377804/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">FIg. 1</figureCitation>
, 
<emphasis id="B960B7738E5C781E82AEFD96FD5FDE02" box="[655,674,602,628]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">A</emphasis>
), which is a diagnostic character of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C1410E28E5C781E8087FDB6FE01DEE3" authority="(Kiefer, 1932)" baseAuthorityName="Kiefer" baseAuthorityYear="1932" box="[166,508,634,661]" class="Hexanauplia" family="Diaptomidae" genus="Sinodiaptomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Calanoida" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B960B7738E5C781E8087FDB6FEA9DEE2" box="[166,340,634,660]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Sinodiaptomus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF8516908E5C781E8140FDB6FE09DEE3" author="Kiefer, F." box="[353,500,634,661]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="213 - 220" refId="ref4120" refString="Kiefer, F. 1932. Versuch eines Systems der altweltlichen Diaptomiden (Copepoda Calanoida). Zoologischer Anzeiger, 100, 213 - 220 [In German]." type="journal article" year="1932">Kiefer, 1932</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. This somite with moderately developed wings. Left wing twolobed with inner one round. Right wing relatively pointed. Both lobes with strong hyaline spine (
<figureCitation id="132F77E48E5C781E80D7FD76FEC4DEA3" box="[246,313,698,725]" captionStart="Figs 1–5" captionStartId="3.[174,213,1802,1824]" captionTargetBox="[230,1169,173,1735]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 1–5. Sinodiaptomus sarsi: 1 — habitus of female (A) and male (B); 2 — last prosomal somite and urosome of female; 3 — leg 5, female; 4 — right antennule, male; 5 — leg 5, male." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6377804" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6377804/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">FIg. 2</figureCitation>
). Urosome with three somites, genital somite slightly asymmetrical, with a moderately long hyaline spine on each side, the intermediate somite short. Antennules extending beyond the caudal setae (
<figureCitation id="132F77E48E5C781E8241FD36FD5CDF62" box="[608,673,762,788]" captionStart="Figs 1–5" captionStartId="3.[174,213,1802,1824]" captionTargetBox="[230,1169,173,1735]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 1–5. Sinodiaptomus sarsi: 1 — habitus of female (A) and male (B); 2 — last prosomal somite and urosome of female; 3 — leg 5, female; 4 — right antennule, male; 5 — leg 5, male." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6377804" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6377804/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">FIg. 1</figureCitation>
, 
<emphasis id="B960B7738E5C781E8292FD36FD3BDF62" box="[691,710,762,788]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">A</emphasis>
). Сoxopodite of leg 5 with long, strong, distolateral projection (
<figureCitation id="132F77E48E5C781E8196FCD6FE09DF42" box="[439,500,794,820]" captionStart="Figs 1–5" captionStartId="3.[174,213,1802,1824]" captionTargetBox="[230,1169,173,1735]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 1–5. Sinodiaptomus sarsi: 1 — habitus of female (A) and male (B); 2 — last prosomal somite and urosome of female; 3 — leg 5, female; 4 — right antennule, male; 5 — leg 5, male." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6377804" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6377804/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">FIg. 3</figureCitation>
, arrow).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAB6B618E5C781E80FAFCF6FB4AD842" blockId="2.[166,1225,506,1077]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
Male (
<figureCitation id="132F77E48E5C781E8104FCF6FE9FDF22" box="[293,354,826,852]" captionStart="Figs 1–5" captionStartId="3.[174,213,1802,1824]" captionTargetBox="[230,1169,173,1735]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 1–5. Sinodiaptomus sarsi: 1 — habitus of female (A) and male (B); 2 — last prosomal somite and urosome of female; 3 — leg 5, female; 4 — right antennule, male; 5 — leg 5, male." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6377804" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6377804/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">FIg. 1</figureCitation>
, B). Body length 
<quantity id="4CECC6848E5C781E8212FCF6FD30DF22" box="[563,717,826,853]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9249999999999998" metricValueMax="1.95" metricValueMin="1.9" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" unit="mm" value="1.9249999999999998" valueMax="1.95" valueMin="1.9">1.9–1.95 mm</quantity>
(1.91 ± 
<quantity id="4CECC6848E5C781E8313FCF6FC60DF22" box="[818,925,826,852]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" unit="mm" value="0.02">0.02 mm</quantity>
, n = 20), prosome length 
<quantity id="4CECC6848E5C781E8087FC96FEB1DF02" box="[166,332,858,884]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.26" metricValueMax="1.32" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" unit="mm" value="1.26" valueMax="1.32" valueMin="1.2">1.20–1.32 mm</quantity>
(1.25 ± 
<quantity id="4CECC6848E5C781E818BFC96FDEEDF02" box="[426,531,858,884]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" unit="mm" value="0.04">0.04 mm</quantity>
), prosome width 
<quantity id="4CECC6848E5C781E82FDFC96FC7FDF02" box="[732,898,858,885]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.6499999999999995" metricValueMax="4.8" metricValueMin="4.5" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" unit="mm" value="0.46499999999999997" valueMax="0.48" valueMin="0.45">0.45–0.48 mm</quantity>
(0.46 ± 
<quantity id="4CECC6848E5C781E83C1FC96FBB7DF02" box="[992,1098,858,884]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" unit="mm" value="0.02">0.02 mm</quantity>
). Urosome has a lateral bend to the right. Antennules reach the end of caudal rami. Right antennule geniculated between segments 18 and 19; segment 15 (
<figureCitation id="132F77E48E5C781E8330FC56FCB1DFC3" box="[785,844,922,949]" captionStart="Figs 1–5" captionStartId="3.[174,213,1802,1824]" captionTargetBox="[230,1169,173,1735]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 1–5. Sinodiaptomus sarsi: 1 — habitus of female (A) and male (B); 2 — last prosomal somite and urosome of female; 3 — leg 5, female; 4 — right antennule, male; 5 — leg 5, male." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6377804" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6377804/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">FIg. 4</figureCitation>
) with longer projection than that of segment 14; antepenultimate segment of right male antennule with a comb-like process (
<figureCitation id="132F77E48E5C781E808CFC16FF16DF83" box="[173,235,986,1013]" captionStart="Figs 1–5" captionStartId="3.[174,213,1802,1824]" captionTargetBox="[230,1169,173,1735]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 1–5. Sinodiaptomus sarsi: 1 — habitus of female (A) and male (B); 2 — last prosomal somite and urosome of female; 3 — leg 5, female; 4 — right antennule, male; 5 — leg 5, male." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6377804" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6377804/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">FIg. 4</figureCitation>
). Basipodite of right leg 5 with a wide round process reaching almost the distal end of the exopodite I and with a hyaline lamella on its distal inner margin (
<figureCitation id="132F77E48E5C781E83E7FC36FBF9D863" box="[966,1028,1018,1045]" captionStart="Figs 1–5" captionStartId="3.[174,213,1802,1824]" captionTargetBox="[230,1169,173,1735]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 1–5. Sinodiaptomus sarsi: 1 — habitus of female (A) and male (B); 2 — last prosomal somite and urosome of female; 3 — leg 5, female; 4 — right antennule, male; 5 — leg 5, male." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6377804" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6377804/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">FIg. 5</figureCitation>
). Exopodite II of left leg 5 ending in a lamellate thumb-like process with short posterodistal basal projection.
</paragraph>
